>Description:
When doing the steps below, hitting space toggles the checkbox on and
immediately off.  It would be good if someone with a native windows machine
can try it, since it might be some problem with my remote viewer.
>How-To-Repeat:
* Move preferences out of the way.
* Start DrRacket.
* Quit it.
* Hit tab to get the no-questions checkbox in focus.
* Hit space to try to toggle it.
